8
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:20,440
A dream about the day I was abandoned at the orphanage.

9
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,760
I hardly have any memories from before I was seven,

10
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:33,760
which is when I was adopted abroad??

11
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:38,040
But that day is an exception, I still remember it somewhat.

12
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:45,040
That moment when she pulled her hand away from mine, so coldly.

13
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:54,520
It's so vivid.

14
00:01:58,920 --> 00:01:59,920
So that's why??

15
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:04,160
So that's why I hate letting go.

16
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:06,120
I hate being left behind,

17
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:10,840
left to bear that feeling of loneliness.

18
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:15,800
Are you alright now?

19
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:21,640
I'm with you now, aren't I?

20
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:27,160
Guess it can't be helped, then. We'll just have to stay together.

21
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:30,920
You're going to make me go to work without sleeping a wink?

22
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:33,680
Yes.

23
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:39,440
You know, I often used to have nightmares when I was little, too.

24
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:44,920
I don't remember what they were about exactly,

25
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:48,040
but I'd wake up screaming and crying.

26
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:52,640
And whenever I did, I'd force my family to stay up.

27
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,800
Whenever that happened,

28
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,840
instead of forcefully putting me back to bed

29
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,800
my mom would stay up and play with me all night.

30
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:06,120
So tonight,

31
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:09,960
I'll stay up with you, all night.

32
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,040
All night?

33
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:12,040
All night.

34
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,800
- Let's go! - To where?

35
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,040
Where else?

36
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:21,840
However, once you go in you can't come back out.

37
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:22,880
Follow me.

38
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,120
Now where was that lock?

39
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,160
What is this?

40
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:36,760
The War of the Flowers: Hwatu.

41
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:39,920
To go or no to go? "Go-stop."

42
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:42,280
This philosophical game with all the joys and sorrows of life.

43
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:46,160
Is this what you meant when you said you'd stay up with me?

44
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:47,160
Yes.

45
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,320
Is there anything else you wanted to do?

46
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:51,160
No, no there isn't.

47
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,880
The colors are very intense.

48
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:56,880
If playing cards are all about symbolism,

49
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:58,520
hwatu cards have strong design elements.

50
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:00,040
That doesn't really matter.

51
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:02,880
Now, if I'm to give you a brief overview of the rules??

52
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:05,120
Look here. Do you see five birds?

53
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,800
Three birds, one bird, one bird. That's a "godori."

54
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:10,000
That's five points. No need to learn their names.

55
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,720
And see how it says "gwang" here?

56
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:13,520
Collect five of these, and you get "oh-gwang."

57
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:16,080
That's 15 points for these five cards.

58
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:17,280
These're two really good sets.

59
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:18,840
And then, do you see how some cards are

60
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:20,280
wearing a ribbon across their chest like in the Miss Korea pageant?

61
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:22,200
The ones without any writing are "cho-dan,"

62
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,760
